cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a new stochastic gradient optimization method that is designed to be robust against noise, which is a common problem in robotics and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions applications in regression, classification, and reinforcement learning, which suggests possible sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
